devdoc.details: DataTokenTemplate is an ERC20 compliant token template     Used by the factory contract as a bytecode reference to      deploy new DataTokens.

approve(address,uint256).details: approve     Standard ERC20 approve function with onlyNotPaused modifier.     Can be called only if the contract is not paused.

params.spender: refers to an address that is allowed to spend tokens.
params.value: refers to amount of tokens that could be spent.

approve(address,uint256).return: true if approval is success, false otherwise.

blob().details: blob     It returns the blob (e.g https://123.com).

params.minter: refers to an address that has minter role
params.name: refers to a template DataToken name
params.symbol: refers to a template DataToken symbol

decimals().details: decimals     It returns the token decimals.     how many supported decimal points

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: decreaseAllowance     Standard ERC20 decreaseAllowance function with onlyNotPaused modifier.     Can be called only if the contract is not paused.

params.spender: refers to an address that is allowed to spend tokens.
params.subtractedValue: refers to an subtracted amount of tokens that could be spent.

decreaseAllowance(address,uint256).return: true if allowance is decreased successfully, false otherwise.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).details: increaseAllowance     Standard ERC20 increaseAllowance function with onlyNotPaused modifier.     Can be called only if the contract is not paused.

params.addedValue: refers to an added amount of tokens that could be spent.
params.spender: refers to an address that is allowed to spend tokens.

increaseAllowance(address,uint256).return: true if allowance is increased successfully, false otherwise.

initialize(string,string,address,uint256.details: initialize     Called prior contract initialization (e.g creating new DataToken instance)     Calls private _initialize function. Only if contract is not initialized.

params.minter: refers to an address that has minter rights
params.name: refers to a new DataToken name
params.symbol: refers to a nea DataToken symbol

isInitialized().details: isInitialized     It checks whether the contract is initialized.
isInitialized().return: true if the contract is initialized.

isMinter(address).details: isMinter     It takes the address and checks whether it has a minter role.
isMinter(address).return: true if account has a minter role.

isPaused().details: isPaused     Function checks if the contract is paused.
isPaused().return: true if the contract is paused.

mint(address,uint256).details: mint     Only the minter address can call it.     msg.value should be higher than zero and gt or eq minting fee

params.account: refers to an address that token is going to be minted to.
params.value: refers to amount of tokens that is going to be minted.

name().details: name     It returns the token name.

pause().details: pause     It pauses the contract functionalities (transfer, mint, etc)     Only could be called if the contract is not already paused.     Only called by the minter address.

setMinter(address).details: setMinter     It sets a new token minter address.     Only called be called if the contract is not paused.     Only the current minter can call it.

params.minter: refers to a new token minter address.

symbol().details: symbol     It returns the token symbol.

transfer(address,uint256).details: transfer     Standard ERC20 transfer function with onlyNotPaused modifier.     Can be called only if the contract is not paused.

params.to: refers to an address that tokens are tranfered to.
params.value: refers to amount of tokens being tranfered.

transfer(address,uint256).return: true if transfer is success, false otherwise.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: transfer     Standard ERC20 transferFrom function with onlyNotPaused modifier.     Can be called only if the contract is not paused.

params.from: refers to an address that tokens are tranfered from.
params.to: refers to an address that tokens are tranfered to.
params.value: refers to amount of tokens being tranfered.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).return: true if transfer is success, false otherwise.

unpause().details: unpause     It unpauses the contract.     Only called if the contract is paused.     Only minter can call it.
